272
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,684
[TIRES SCREECHING]

273
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:26,245
Rio, stop!

274
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:54,373
OFFICER: When we got there, we
found the victim

275
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:55,507
lying on the pavement.

276
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:56,642
That's all.

277
00:17:56,675 --> 00:17:58,177
TOM: Who reported it?

278
00:17:58,210 --> 00:17:59,378
OFFICER: Anonymous tip.

279
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:01,313
Nobody wants to get involved.

280
00:18:01,346 --> 00:18:02,548
Were there any witnesses?

281
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:03,649
No, sir.

282
00:18:03,682 --> 00:18:06,351
That's impossible.

283
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:07,653
Sorry, sir.

284
00:18:07,686 --> 00:18:09,788
What about my daughter?

285
00:18:09,822 --> 00:18:11,757
They were together.

286
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:14,626
Like I said, sir, it was just
the victim at the scene.

287
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:15,561
- That's crazy! - All right.

288
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:16,495
All right.

289
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:18,230
Calm down, Rio.

290
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:20,299
We'll find Sakura.

291
00:18:20,332 --> 00:18:21,266
Don't you worry.

292
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,201
We'll find her.

293
00:18:31,343 --> 00:18:32,244
I'm sorry.

294
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:57,369
[FANS HUMMING]

295
00:19:18,724 --> 00:19:22,294
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:19:40,646 --> 00:19:44,249
[FOOTSTEPS]

297
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:55,294
Rio, I'm so sorry.

298
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:58,530
[SEAGULLS CALLING]

299
00:19:58,564 --> 00:20:04,570
We were married 30 years.

300
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:08,574
This our first trip outside
Japan.

301
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:17,549
I killed her.

302
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:19,785
Rio, don't.

303
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:20,819
Oh, god, Tom.

304
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:36,735
[CONVERSATIONS IN DISTANCE]

305
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:52,417
Is that Sakura's?

306
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:53,385
Yeah.

307
00:20:56,655 --> 00:20:58,624
I'm afraid we have to assume
that she

308
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:00,325
was kidnapped by the suspects.

309
00:21:03,829 --> 00:21:07,399
- Is that all you found? - Yes,
sir.

310
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:10,002
Is there something missing?

311
00:21:10,035 --> 00:21:11,503
Yeah.

312
00:21:11,536 --> 00:21:13,705
The camera.

313
00:21:13,739 --> 00:21:15,674
What kind of a camera?

314
00:21:15,707 --> 00:21:21,647
It's Konica-- pocket camera,
made in Japan.

315
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:25,017
Check the local pawn shops in
that area.

316
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:26,551
And give this to the lab.

317
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:27,686
I want it developed.

318
00:21:27,719 --> 00:21:28,654
Yes, sir.

319
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:52,344
RIO: Oh, my daughter.

320
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:26,545
Thank you.

321
00:22:33,552 --> 00:22:35,587
I heard what happened.

322
00:22:35,620 --> 00:22:36,722
Yeah.

323
00:22:36,755 --> 00:22:40,559
I don't know what to say except
I'm sorry it happened.

324
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:51,837
Any clues yet?

325
00:22:51,870 --> 00:22:55,173
Well, we're doing everything
that we can.

326
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:56,808
I see.

327
00:22:56,842 --> 00:22:57,776
Of course.

328
00:23:19,731 --> 00:23:22,701
[MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:23:22,734 --> 00:23:26,138
[LIGHTER STRIKING]

330
00:24:17,055 --> 00:24:18,623
Uh, Inspector Yuki?

331
00:24:18,657 --> 00:24:20,859
Inspector Yuki?

332
00:24:20,892 --> 00:24:22,627
The chief thought you might do--

333
00:24:22,661 --> 00:24:27,098
I mean, thought you might need
something.

334
00:24:27,132 --> 00:24:28,633
Hey, hey!

335
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:30,836
Inspector Yuki! Wait.

336
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:32,270
Where are you going?

337
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:54,192
Uh, Inspector Yuki?

338
00:24:54,226 --> 00:24:57,195
Uh, Inspector Yuki!

339
00:25:42,741 --> 00:25:43,675
Why?

340
00:25:46,745 --> 00:25:47,646
Why what, sir?

341
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:56,621
Why was my wife killed?

342
00:25:56,655 --> 00:25:59,291
Well, I hate to say it but
maybe for as little

343
00:25:59,324 --> 00:26:01,293
as that camera.

344
00:26:01,326 --> 00:26:03,929
Camera?

345
00:26:03,962 --> 00:26:07,832
Who would shoot someone just for
camera?

346
00:26:07,866 --> 00:26:09,935
Hey, in America these days, you
can get killed

347
00:26:09,968 --> 00:26:11,703
for a pack of cigarettes.

348
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:43,435
Hey, Mr. Menza.

349
00:26:43,468 --> 00:26:45,870
Yeah, what's up, Frank?

350
00:26:45,904 --> 00:26:48,773
Oh, I sure hope Mr. Foley can
do

351
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:51,376
something to help our senior
citizens out, Mr. Menza.

352
00:26:51,409 --> 00:26:53,178
It's tough on old people these
days.

353
00:26:53,211 --> 00:26:55,814
Look, you just make sure that
you and your old friends

354
00:26:55,847 --> 00:26:57,382
vote for him as mayor.

355
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:58,750
Then he'll do something.

356
00:27:02,253 --> 00:27:03,154
I love it.

357
00:27:03,188 --> 00:27:04,723
Beth.

358
00:27:04,756 --> 00:27:08,827
Hey, Lenny, where's the old man?

359
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:10,028
Oh, Danny, boy!

360
00:27:10,061 --> 00:27:10,962
Catch.

361
00:27:10,996 --> 00:27:11,863
Larry.

362
00:27:11,896 --> 00:27:12,831
Got a second?

363
00:27:12,864 --> 00:27:13,832
What's up?

364
00:27:13,865 --> 00:27:14,766
How are the kids?

365
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:16,267
- Good, good. - OK.

366
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:17,502
- You? - Fine, fine.

367
00:27:17,535 --> 00:27:21,406
Listen, Danny, I want you to
watch out for those old bitches

368
00:27:21,439 --> 00:27:23,808
from the women's organization.

369
00:27:23,842 --> 00:27:25,377
They're distributing that drug
strategy booklet

370
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:26,778
to all the city officers.

371
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:27,712
Look, I got news for you.

372
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:28,713
They've already been here.

373
00:27:28,747 --> 00:27:29,914
[GROANING]

374
00:27:29,948 --> 00:27:32,250
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, don't
worry about it, all right?

375
00:27:32,283 --> 00:27:35,720
The old man's keeping a low
profile until he retires.

376
00:27:35,754 --> 00:27:37,155
He won't do a thing.

377
00:27:37,188 --> 00:27:38,089
True?

378
00:27:38,123 --> 00:27:38,990
Trust me.

379
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:41,960
Ah, Danny, I love you.

380
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:43,361
Hey, find a home for this, will
you?

381
00:27:43,395 --> 00:27:44,496
Sure.

382
00:27:44,529 --> 00:27:49,467
LARRY: (SINGING) Oh, Danny boy,
the pipes are playing.

383
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:52,470
All hail to the chief.

384
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:54,873
When you want to see me, you
make an appointment

385
00:27:54,906 --> 00:27:56,374
with my receptionist.

386
00:27:56,408 --> 00:27:58,343
Hey, I only talk to secretaries

387
00:27:58,376 --> 00:28:02,213
when I need a little, uh, stress
reduction in my private office.

388
00:28:02,247 --> 00:28:03,782
I got something for you.

389
00:28:03,815 --> 00:28:04,983
What's this?

390
00:28:05,016 --> 00:28:08,420
Well, an invitation to Foley's
campaign party next week.

391
00:28:08,453 --> 00:28:10,388
Be there or be square.

392
00:28:10,422 --> 00:28:12,490
Campaign for what?

393
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:14,325
You haven't heard?

394
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:16,428
Mr. Foley is going to be our
next mayor.

395
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:25,904
You would be wise not to
underestimate Mr. Foley.

396
00:28:25,937 --> 00:28:29,207
I have something for you.

397
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:32,911
You give this to Mr. Foley, that
esteemed

398
00:28:32,944 --> 00:28:34,179
member of our city council.

399
00:28:37,849 --> 00:28:39,050
What's this all about,
Bradfield?

400
00:28:39,084 --> 00:28:43,388
Oh, I suggest you read that
very carefully.

401
00:28:43,421 --> 00:28:47,459
Yeah, well, I have a little
suggestion for you.

402
00:28:47,492 --> 00:28:50,161
You have six long months before
you

403
00:28:50,195 --> 00:28:53,364
can collect that ill-deserved
pension of yours.

404
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:56,935
Now, I suggest that you be a
little more courteous.

405
00:29:00,338 --> 00:29:04,209
Remember, Thomas, courtesy pays.

406
00:29:17,422 --> 00:29:21,426
[MURMURING]

407
00:29:23,394 --> 00:29:24,496
CHARLIE: Cindy!

408
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:25,563
Jeez.

409
00:29:25,597 --> 00:29:28,433
What, do you serve the good guys
last around here?

410
00:29:28,466 --> 00:29:32,904
I'm going to get gray hair
before you serve us any coffee.

411
00:29:32,937 --> 00:29:36,307
Any news in the investigation?

412
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:37,375
Yeah.

413
00:29:37,408 --> 00:29:40,612
According to the lab, the gun
used was modified.

414
00:29:40,645 --> 00:29:42,080
Modified?

415
00:29:42,113 --> 00:29:42,914
Yeah.

416
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:44,182
That's a felony good for 20
years.

417
00:29:44,215 --> 00:29:48,052
If the gun's used in a homicide,
it carries the death sentence.

418
00:29:48,086 --> 00:29:49,287
So?

419
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:52,390
So our killer's probably a gun
nut.

420
00:29:52,423 --> 00:29:55,093
How many gun nuts are there?

421
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:58,229
There were five homicides last
night alone.

422
00:29:58,263 --> 00:30:03,868
You mean a foreigner death
comes last?

423
00:30:03,902 --> 00:30:06,638
You've got Chief Bradfield on
your side.

424
00:30:06,671 --> 00:30:08,139
All right.

425
00:30:08,173 --> 00:30:08,940
Now, look.

426
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:12,043
Three of them turned gray
already.

427
00:30:12,076 --> 00:30:13,411
Ow!

428
00:30:13,444 --> 00:30:14,412
Special service.

429
00:30:14,445 --> 00:30:15,346
Jeez.

430
00:30:15,380 --> 00:30:18,516
[BEEPING]

431
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,552
Oh, I just got paged by
headquarters.

432
00:30:28,293 --> 00:30:32,230
Hey something wrong?

433
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:35,500
You look like you're on your way
to a funeral or something.

434
00:30:35,533 --> 00:30:38,136
Oh, I just came from one.

435
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:39,604
Oh.

436
00:30:39,637 --> 00:30:40,538
Excuse me.

437
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:52,584
A guy just brought your wife's
Konica camera into a pawnshop.

438
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:53,918
He has it?

439
00:30:53,952 --> 00:30:54,919
No.

440
00:30:54,953 --> 00:30:56,554
He got scared and left the shop
with the camera.

441
00:30:56,588 --> 00:30:58,122
That doesn't help us.

442
00:30:58,156 --> 00:30:59,157
Well, maybe it does.

443
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:01,059
The owner of the pawnshop
recognized the guy.

444
00:31:01,092 --> 00:31:04,028
He's an ex-con by the name of
Clyde Jones.

445
00:31:04,062 --> 00:31:05,163
Where is he?

446
00:31:05,196 --> 00:31:06,998
Well, he hangs out at a place
just down the street.

447
00:31:07,031 --> 00:31:08,099
Hey, wait!

448
00:31:08,132 --> 00:31:09,033
Cindy.

449
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:16,140
To the right!

450
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:18,676
To the right!

451
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:19,611
To the right!

452
00:31:19,644 --> 00:31:20,578
Yeah!

453
00:31:27,485 --> 00:31:28,353
OK.

454
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:29,387
In here.

455
00:31:32,523 --> 00:31:33,558
Wait. Wait.

456
00:31:33,591 --> 00:31:35,226
All right, look.

457
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:38,229
Maybe we should call for backup.

458
00:31:38,263 --> 00:31:39,497
What for?

459
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:41,132
Well, you never know,
especially

460
00:31:41,165 --> 00:31:43,601
in this neighborhood.

461
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,536
I will wait there.

462
00:31:55,046 --> 00:31:58,416
[CLACKING]

463
00:32:24,575 --> 00:32:26,110
Police officer.

464
00:32:26,144 --> 00:32:28,746
You're wanted in connection with
a murder investigation.

465
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:34,452
What's that in your pocket, huh?

466
00:32:34,485 --> 00:32:35,486
Is that a camera?

467
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:37,488
Where'd you get that camera?

468
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:39,724
[THUDDING]

469
00:32:39,757 --> 00:32:40,758
Oh!

470
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:43,394
Goddamn it.

471
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:45,096
Look out!

472
00:32:45,129 --> 00:32:46,531
[GRUNTING]

473
00:32:47,532 --> 00:32:51,102
[MUSIC PLAYING]

474
00:33:04,482 --> 00:33:05,483
That's our man!

475
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:44,389
Coming through!

476
00:33:44,422 --> 00:33:46,491
[SHOUTING] Sorry!

477
00:33:46,524 --> 00:33:47,392
MAN: Hey, watch out!

478
00:33:47,425 --> 00:33:50,194
Police officer.

479
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:51,162
Watch it!

480
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:02,507
Police! Coming through!

481
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:03,508
Excuse me.

482
00:34:03,541 --> 00:34:04,542
Police officer.

483
00:35:00,531 --> 00:35:01,466
Oh.

484
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:16,414
Oh!

485
00:35:33,397 --> 00:35:36,400
[GRUNTING]

486
00:35:41,639 --> 00:35:43,441
Where is my daughter?

487
00:35:43,474 --> 00:35:45,209
I don't know.

488
00:35:45,243 --> 00:35:48,246
I swear I don't know.

489
00:35:48,279 --> 00:35:49,280
Where's-- [GUNSHOT]

490
00:35:49,313 --> 00:35:49,981
CHARLIE: Sorry.

491
00:35:50,014 --> 00:35:52,917
Don't shoot me!

492
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:54,785
Hold it.

493
00:35:54,819 --> 00:35:58,356
Hey, that's Sakura's camera.

494
00:35:58,389 --> 00:35:59,657
Where did you get this camera?

495
00:35:59,690 --> 00:36:00,758
I swear I don't know.

496
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:01,726
I just found it.

497
00:36:04,795 --> 00:36:06,697
Answer.

498
00:36:06,731 --> 00:36:07,665
I don't know.

499
00:36:07,698 --> 00:36:08,866
You shot my wife.

500
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:09,934
No, no. I didn't.

501
00:36:09,967 --> 00:36:10,868
I didn't.

502
00:36:10,902 --> 00:36:11,969
I had nothing to do with it.

503
00:36:12,003 --> 00:36:13,337
I-- I found the camera.

504
00:36:13,371 --> 00:36:14,238
I just picked it up.

505
00:36:14,272 --> 00:36:15,640
I swear.

506
00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:18,676
I swear. - Where?

507
00:36:18,709 --> 00:36:22,580
In-- in-- in the burned up
factory in Charlestown.

508
00:36:22,613 --> 00:36:24,015
I'm telling the truth!

509
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:26,250
Inspector, give me the gun.

510
00:36:26,284 --> 00:36:28,452
I can't let you interrogate the
suspect.

511
00:36:28,486 --> 00:36:31,556
[GRUNTING] - Come on.

512
00:36:35,526 --> 00:36:36,427
Don't move.

513
00:36:40,064 --> 00:36:42,500
Let's go.

514
00:36:42,533 --> 00:36:44,702
What?

515
00:36:44,735 --> 00:36:46,871
Rio stole your gun?

516
00:36:46,904 --> 00:36:48,339
He surprised me.

517
00:36:48,372 --> 00:36:50,875
I-- I guess he just flipped out,
Chief.

518
00:36:50,908 --> 00:36:52,977
TOM (ON PHONE): Do you have any
idea where he was headed?

519
00:36:53,010 --> 00:36:54,745
Well, I think he went to the
abandoned

520
00:36:54,779 --> 00:36:56,814
factory in Charlestown.

521
00:36:56,847 --> 00:36:58,015
TOM (ON PHONE): Charlestown?

522
00:36:58,049 --> 00:36:58,950
All right.

523
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:02,853
Charlestown.

524
00:37:06,791 --> 00:37:09,493
Tom, is something wrong,
darling?

525
00:37:09,527 --> 00:37:12,930
Yes, and I'd better find Rio
before he

526
00:37:12,964 --> 00:37:16,033
really gets into trouble.

527
00:37:16,067 --> 00:37:16,934
Sorry, dear.

528
00:37:16,968 --> 00:37:18,469
[KISSING]

529
00:37:20,838 --> 00:37:24,408
[MUSIC PLAYING]

530
00:37:40,891 --> 00:37:41,759
[GRUNTING]

531
00:37:41,792 --> 00:37:42,727
SUSPECT: I don't know.

532
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,729
It was somewhere around here. I
don't know.

533
00:37:47,698 --> 00:37:49,333
[GRUNTING]

534
00:37:49,367 --> 00:37:50,301
Jeez.

535
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:21,932
[GUNSHOT]

536
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:24,935
[SCREAMING]

537
00:38:28,906 --> 00:38:30,941
Hey, let's go.

538
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:32,543
SUSPECT: (WHISPERING) Oh, shit.

539
00:38:32,576 --> 00:38:34,512
Come on.

540
00:38:34,545 --> 00:38:35,546
[SCREAMING]

541
00:38:35,579 --> 00:38:36,514
WOMAN: No!

542
00:38:36,547 --> 00:38:37,448
No!

543
00:38:39,684 --> 00:38:42,586
[MEN GRUNTING]

544
00:38:42,620 --> 00:38:44,522
Hey, man, this kind of stuff
happens all the time!

545
00:38:44,555 --> 00:38:45,289
Shut up.

546
00:38:47,725 --> 00:38:48,793
SUSPECT: I don't want any
problems

547
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:50,861
with the bad dudes around here!

548
00:38:50,895 --> 00:38:53,531
RIO: Shut up.

549
00:38:53,564 --> 00:38:54,465
Come on.

550
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:55,399
Come on.

551
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:58,602
WOMAN: No!

552
00:38:58,636 --> 00:39:01,405
No!

553
00:39:01,439 --> 00:39:02,707
[SCREAMING]

554
00:39:02,740 --> 00:39:03,641
No!

555
00:39:16,153 --> 00:39:17,555
Your buddies?

556
00:39:17,588 --> 00:39:18,456
No.

557
00:39:18,489 --> 00:39:19,590
I don't know them.

558
00:39:19,623 --> 00:39:21,025
I just found the camera here.

559
00:39:21,058 --> 00:39:22,526
- Come on. - Come on!

560
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,461
Come on.

561
00:39:23,494 --> 00:39:24,195
Please, let me go.

562
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:27,431
[GRUNTING]

563
00:39:29,233 --> 00:39:32,436
[YELLING]

564
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:43,781
RIO: Go.

565
00:39:48,219 --> 00:40:02,199
[GRUNTING]

566
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:03,667
WOMAN: No!

567
00:40:03,701 --> 00:40:04,635
No!

568
00:40:07,638 --> 00:40:09,673
No!

569
00:40:09,707 --> 00:40:10,574
No!

570
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:11,609
[GUNSHOTS]

571
00:40:13,110 --> 00:40:13,978
[GUNSHOT]

572
00:40:14,011 --> 00:40:15,980
[GRUNTING]

573
00:40:16,013 --> 00:40:17,014
RIO: Don't move.

574
00:40:20,017 --> 00:40:22,987
[GRUNTING]

575
00:40:32,596 --> 00:40:35,599
[CRYING]

576
00:41:09,333 --> 00:41:11,535
[BOTTLES CLANGING]

577
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:23,881
Take those cuffs off.

578
00:41:23,914 --> 00:41:25,182
Well, they said the one guy's
going to be

579
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:27,618
in the hospital for a month.

580
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:28,919
And the guy you shot in the knee
is

581
00:41:28,953 --> 00:41:32,089
going to be a cripple for life.

582
00:41:32,122 --> 00:41:35,693
Do you understand what you did,
Rio?

583
00:41:35,726 --> 00:41:38,963
You can be indicted for
attempted murder, for assault

584
00:41:38,996 --> 00:41:40,064
with a deadly weapon.

585
00:41:40,097 --> 00:41:43,267
Are you trying to get my pension
taken away from me?

586
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:46,237
Are you trying to ruin Hanna and
my retirement?

587
00:41:46,270 --> 00:41:49,807
After all, Hanna waited 30 years
for this, just like Hiroko.

588
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,775
My wife is dead.

589
00:41:51,809 --> 00:41:54,078
My daughter has been kidnapped.

590
00:41:54,111 --> 00:41:55,980
I know, my friend.

591
00:41:56,013 --> 00:41:58,916
And I deeply sympathize with
you.

592
00:41:58,949 --> 00:42:01,852
But I can't let you take the law
into your own hands.

593
00:42:01,886 --> 00:42:04,121
I don't need your sympathy.

594
00:42:04,154 --> 00:42:06,957
I want my daughter back.

595
00:42:06,991 --> 00:42:10,027
You have to stay out of it.

596
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:12,263
Now, the official word is that
Charlie

597
00:42:12,296 --> 00:42:14,331
did it with his own gun.

598
00:42:14,365 --> 00:42:20,170
All I want you to do is leave
this in my hands

599
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:25,009
and go back to the hotel,
please, my friend.

600
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:26,877
OK, Tom.

601
00:42:26,911 --> 00:42:29,179
But wait.

602
00:42:29,213 --> 00:42:34,885
They stole the camera and took
out the film.

603
00:42:34,919 --> 00:42:37,955
Isn't it strange?

604
00:42:37,988 --> 00:42:41,392
Check this, please.

605
00:42:41,425 --> 00:42:42,359
Please, Tom.

606
00:42:45,729 --> 00:42:46,764
All right, my friend.

607
00:42:46,797 --> 00:42:47,698
All right, I will.

608
00:42:50,334 --> 00:42:51,769
LAB TECHNICIAN: No prints could
be saved

609
00:42:51,802 --> 00:42:52,903
from the roll of film he found.

610
00:42:52,937 --> 00:42:54,138
TOM: Yeah.

611
00:42:54,171 --> 00:42:55,039
All right.

612
00:42:55,072 --> 00:42:56,407
Show him what you've got.

613
00:42:56,440 --> 00:42:57,341
All right.

614
00:42:57,374 --> 00:43:00,210
Here are the prints from the
belongings.

615
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:04,615
I enlarged this one because it
seems peculiar here.

616
00:43:09,019 --> 00:43:11,989
Who are these men?

617
00:43:12,022 --> 00:43:14,758
Some kind of exchange?

618
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:17,027
TOM: Yeah, it could be, I guess.

619
00:43:17,061 --> 00:43:18,362
Any idea where this was taken?

620
00:43:18,395 --> 00:43:20,264
LAB TECHNICIAN: Looks like a
park near Charles

621
00:43:20,297 --> 00:43:25,135
River, maybe Boston Park.

622
00:43:25,169 --> 00:43:27,104
Boston Park?

623
00:43:27,137 --> 00:43:28,038
What is it?

624
00:43:31,442 --> 00:43:33,644
Uh, it's nothing.

625
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:11,215
Rio, stop.

626
00:44:14,284 --> 00:44:17,254
I will save my daughter myself.

627
00:44:17,287 --> 00:44:20,057
Rio, I can't let you.

628
00:44:20,090 --> 00:44:21,725
Don't worry.

629
00:44:21,759 --> 00:44:24,995
I won't cause you any trouble.

630
00:44:25,029 --> 00:44:27,164
And I won't mess up your
pension.

631
00:44:32,469 --> 00:44:34,004
Stop Rio.

632
00:44:34,038 --> 00:44:34,872
That's right.

633
00:44:34,905 --> 00:44:38,308
If he resists, throw him in a
cell.

634
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:39,209
RIO: Tom!

635
00:44:39,243 --> 00:44:41,378
OFFICER: Knock it off.

636
00:44:41,412 --> 00:44:42,312
RIO: Come on.

637
00:44:42,346 --> 00:44:43,347
Stop!

638
00:44:43,380 --> 00:44:44,848
OFFICER: Come on. Come on.

639
00:44:44,882 --> 00:44:46,050
RIO: Hey!

640
00:44:46,083 --> 00:44:46,984
Tom!

641
00:44:47,017 --> 00:44:48,285
OFFICER: Knock it off.

642
00:44:48,318 --> 00:44:50,921
[GRUNTING]

643
00:44:53,991 --> 00:44:55,993
RIO: Tom!

644
00:44:56,026 --> 00:44:57,227
Come on, Tom!

645
00:45:02,332 --> 00:45:05,436
Get the chief!

646
00:45:05,469 --> 00:45:10,407
I want to see Tom Bradfield!

647
00:45:10,441 --> 00:45:12,409
Hey!

648
00:45:12,443 --> 00:45:14,278
Hey, come on, Tom!

649
00:46:04,495 --> 00:46:05,529
(WHISPERING) Yes.

650
00:46:05,562 --> 00:46:06,497
Yes.

651
00:46:09,466 --> 00:46:13,070
[MUSIC PLAYING]

652
00:46:20,511 --> 00:46:21,445
Yeah.

653
00:46:28,085 --> 00:46:28,986
Yes!

654
00:46:40,931 --> 00:46:44,902
[SEAGULLS CALLING]

655
00:47:02,319 --> 00:47:03,320
MAN: Oh, goddamnit!

656
00:47:03,353 --> 00:47:04,254
Oh!

657
00:47:22,272 --> 00:47:23,173
Open this up.

658
00:47:30,647 --> 00:47:31,949
Something wrong?

659
00:48:13,290 --> 00:48:16,493
This is not Sakura.

660
00:48:16,526 --> 00:48:18,362
[EXHALING]

661
00:48:18,395 --> 00:48:20,497
Thank god she's still alive.

662
00:48:20,530 --> 00:48:21,465
Yeah.

663
00:48:25,035 --> 00:48:26,036
She's alive.

664
00:48:34,011 --> 00:48:34,711
[ENGINE STARTING]

665
00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:38,715
[SIRENS BLARING]

666
00:48:43,587 --> 00:48:45,022
TOM: There's something I must
tell you.

667
00:48:47,624 --> 00:48:53,630
The suspects are part of a major
drug operation in this city.

668
00:48:53,664 --> 00:48:56,600
What?

669
00:48:56,633 --> 00:48:59,703
Boston Park is overrun with
drug dealers.

670
00:49:02,439 --> 00:49:05,609
When I saw that enlargement in
my office,

671
00:49:05,642 --> 00:49:09,313
I realized that Hiroko had
accidentally

672
00:49:09,346 --> 00:49:13,450
photographed a very influential
man involved

673
00:49:13,483 --> 00:49:17,154
in a drug deal going down.

674
00:49:17,187 --> 00:49:21,158
What are you telling me?

675
00:49:21,191 --> 00:49:23,193
I think what I'm telling you is
that I'm not going to be

676
00:49:23,226 --> 00:49:27,164
able to be much help to you.

677
00:49:27,197 --> 00:49:29,800
That influential man that she
photographed

678
00:49:29,833 --> 00:49:33,537
happens to be the right arm of
the most

679
00:49:33,570 --> 00:49:37,407
powerful man in this city.

680
00:49:37,441 --> 00:49:42,145
He is so powerful that some of
my own cops are in on it--

681
00:49:42,179 --> 00:49:44,147
cops that were here before I
took over.

682
00:49:47,417 --> 00:49:54,057
Now, if I start poking around, I
may be forced to retire.

683
00:49:54,091 --> 00:49:57,160
I lose everything.

684
00:49:57,194 --> 00:50:00,731
But I haven't helped you one
bit.

685
00:50:03,734 --> 00:50:06,103
Let me do it.

686
00:50:06,136 --> 00:50:07,771
Hm-mm.

687
00:50:07,804 --> 00:50:09,239
I knew you would say that.

688
00:50:11,842 --> 00:50:15,078
But I can't officially ask you
to do that.

689
00:50:15,112 --> 00:50:17,547
I see.

690
00:50:17,581 --> 00:50:21,084
Just tell me who they are.

691
00:50:25,522 --> 00:50:26,423
All right.

692
00:50:31,795 --> 00:50:34,531
His name is Joe Foley.

693
00:50:34,564 --> 00:50:37,501
He's on the city council.

694
00:50:37,534 --> 00:50:40,570
Everything that you need to know
about him and his organization

695
00:50:40,604 --> 00:50:45,108
is in that envelope. - Joe
Foley.

696
00:50:48,311 --> 00:50:50,447
All right.

697
00:50:50,480 --> 00:50:53,250
I'll take it from here.

698
00:50:53,283 --> 00:50:56,319
Thank you for telling me.

699
00:50:56,353 --> 00:50:57,320
There's one thing more.

700
00:51:10,167 --> 00:51:15,705
These men are very, very
dangerous.

701
00:51:15,739 --> 00:51:19,576
I'm no longer afraid of
anything

702
00:51:19,609 --> 00:51:23,880
except for my daughter.

703
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:25,782
Many thanks, Tom.

704
00:51:30,787 --> 00:51:34,391
[MUSIC PLAYING]

705
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:23,340
[CLAPPING]

706
00:52:23,373 --> 00:52:25,475
And I will.

707
00:52:25,509 --> 00:52:28,512
All the promises I have made are
true.

708
00:52:28,545 --> 00:52:31,414
I'll not go back on any of them.

709
00:52:31,448 --> 00:52:33,416
Read my lips.

710
00:52:33,450 --> 00:52:37,254
[CLAPPING CONTINUES]

711
00:52:37,287 --> 00:52:38,788
Thank you very much--

712
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:39,689
very much.

713
00:52:39,723 --> 00:52:43,326
[ENGINE STARTING]

714
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:53,703
[MUSIC PLAYING]

715
00:53:16,626 --> 00:53:19,796
LARRY: Mr. Foley, welcome, sir.

716
00:53:19,829 --> 00:53:21,898
JOE: Thank you.

717
00:53:21,932 --> 00:53:26,503
The honorable Thomas Bradfield
is being an asshole, sir.

718
00:53:26,536 --> 00:53:29,339
Well, we'll just have to
straighten him out, won't we?

719
00:53:31,741 --> 00:53:32,742
Thank you.

720
00:53:53,330 --> 00:53:54,998
You trying to pull something,
Tom?

721
00:53:57,801 --> 00:54:04,441
I mean, if you got something you
want to say to me, speak up.

722
00:54:04,474 --> 00:54:05,375
Go on.

723
00:54:05,408 --> 00:54:06,443
Say it.

724
00:54:06,476 --> 00:54:08,278
I don't know what you're
talking about, Foley.

725
00:54:12,616 --> 00:54:18,388
Think hard before you try to
blackmail me.

726
00:54:18,421 --> 00:54:21,658
After all, Chief, some members
of your narcotics

727
00:54:21,691 --> 00:54:24,661
squad are, shall we say,
associated with us.

728
00:54:24,694 --> 00:54:26,463
You wouldn't want that
publicized, would you?

729
00:54:29,499 --> 00:54:31,034
I guess not.

730
00:54:31,067 --> 00:54:33,036
LARRY: No, I guess not.

731
00:54:33,069 --> 00:54:38,675
Then we can expect you at the
campaign party next week?

732
00:54:38,708 --> 00:54:43,980
I might-- might sell you my own
yacht at a very low price.

733
00:54:44,014 --> 00:54:44,948
Ow.

734
00:54:48,918 --> 00:54:50,854
I don't want your fucking boat,
Foley.

735
00:54:57,027 --> 00:55:02,532
You will pay for that, Tom.

736
00:55:12,876 --> 00:55:15,812
It's not a threat.

737
00:55:15,845 --> 00:55:16,846
It's a promise.

738
00:55:22,419 --> 00:55:23,386
[DOOR SLAMMING]

739
00:55:27,157 --> 00:55:28,358
[GRUNTING]

740
00:55:38,101 --> 00:55:41,671
[MUSIC PLAYING]

741
00:55:49,045 --> 00:55:52,615
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

742
00:55:59,956 --> 00:56:03,593
[PHONE RINGING]

743
00:56:03,626 --> 00:56:04,561
Hello?

744
00:56:04,594 --> 00:56:05,495
TOM (ON PHONE): Hi.

745
00:56:05,528 --> 00:56:06,896
It's me.

746
00:56:06,930 --> 00:56:08,164
What's the matter, darling?

747
00:56:08,198 --> 00:56:09,666
You sound strange.

748
00:56:09,699 --> 00:56:11,701
Well, as a matter of fact--

749
00:56:11,735 --> 00:56:13,136
HANNA (ON PHONE): You know, I
was just looking

750
00:56:13,169 --> 00:56:15,438
at these brochures on Europe.

751
00:56:15,472 --> 00:56:17,207
They really look good.

752
00:56:17,240 --> 00:56:18,775
Wouldn't you rather go there
instead

753
00:56:18,808 --> 00:56:20,810
of buying some silly old boat?

754
00:56:20,844 --> 00:56:24,914
Hanna, we may have to forget
about the boat.

755
00:56:24,948 --> 00:56:30,520
Uh, we may have to forget about
Europe, too.

756
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:34,090
I-- I just wanted you to be
prepared for that.

757
00:56:34,124 --> 00:56:37,961
This has something to do with
Rio, doesn't it, Tom?

758
00:56:37,994 --> 00:56:42,999
Honey, just be prepared.

759
00:56:43,032 --> 00:56:48,505
HANNA (ON PHONE): Tom, please,
be careful.

760
00:56:48,538 --> 00:56:49,472
Yeah.

761
00:56:54,110 --> 00:56:55,078
[KNOCKING]

762
00:56:57,013 --> 00:56:58,782
What did you do to Mr. Foley?

763
00:56:58,815 --> 00:56:59,783
He's as mad as hell.

764
00:56:59,816 --> 00:57:01,885
He says he's going to sue the
shit out of you.

765
00:57:01,918 --> 00:57:03,787
You're through, Largent.

766
00:57:03,820 --> 00:57:04,754
What was that, Chief?

767
00:57:04,788 --> 00:57:07,824
Get me Internal Affairs.

768
00:57:07,857 --> 00:57:10,260
This is Chief Bradfield.

769
00:57:10,293 --> 00:57:14,664
I want the entire narcotics
squad suspended.

770
00:57:14,697 --> 00:57:16,099
The charges?

771
00:57:16,132 --> 00:57:18,902
Suspicion of drug trafficking.

772
00:57:18,935 --> 00:57:21,571
Yes, that's right.

773
00:57:21,604 --> 00:57:22,705
Yes!

774
00:57:22,739 --> 00:57:24,808
I want a full-blown
investigation.

775
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:25,942
You're crazy, Chief.

776
00:57:25,975 --> 00:57:27,577
You know what's going to happen
to you if you do that?

777
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:29,045
Get your ass out of here.

778
00:57:29,078 --> 00:57:30,780
You're due to retire in six
months, Chief.

779
00:57:30,814 --> 00:57:31,714
Don't blow it.

780
00:57:31,748 --> 00:57:33,183
You make me sick!

781
00:57:37,787 --> 00:57:39,856
You're through.

782
00:57:39,889 --> 00:57:40,890
Yes, sir.

783
00:58:42,785 --> 00:58:44,187
[ENGINE STARTING]

784
00:58:53,763 --> 00:58:55,765
[ENGINE STARTING]

785
00:58:58,768 --> 00:59:02,171
[MUSIC PLAYING]

786
01:00:05,068 --> 01:00:07,670
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

787
01:00:09,806 --> 01:00:10,807
Thank you, John.

788
01:00:14,143 --> 01:00:15,678
Dear.

789
01:00:15,712 --> 01:00:18,181
I don't think we need you any
further, John.

790
01:00:43,072 --> 01:00:46,676
[SUGGESTIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

791
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:00,390
Mama.

792
01:01:36,192 --> 01:01:39,829
Well, what might we have here--
a late-night visitor?

793
01:01:39,862 --> 01:01:43,499
I here to present, um,
insurance company.

794
01:01:43,533 --> 01:01:44,500
[LAUGHING]

795
01:01:44,534 --> 01:01:45,802
That's very original.

796
01:01:45,835 --> 01:01:47,904
Come on.

797
01:01:47,937 --> 01:01:50,139
You know, I hope you carry a lot
of insurance

798
01:01:50,173 --> 01:01:52,075
because it's time for you to say
good night.

799
01:01:52,108 --> 01:01:53,076
[GRUNTING]

800
01:01:55,945 --> 01:01:57,280
(WHISPERING) Hi, Inspector.

801
01:01:57,313 --> 01:01:59,449
Charlie, how?

802
01:01:59,482 --> 01:02:01,384
Well, when I saw you hiding
from me in your car in front

803
01:02:01,417 --> 01:02:04,220
of headquarters, I figured you
had a good reason,

804
01:02:04,253 --> 01:02:05,822
so I didn't bother you.

805
01:02:05,855 --> 01:02:08,858
But I did tail you.

806
01:02:08,891 --> 01:02:09,992
OK.

807
01:02:10,026 --> 01:02:12,361
Give it up.

808
01:02:12,395 --> 01:02:13,396
[GRUNTING]

809
01:02:18,968 --> 01:02:20,336
[CHUCKLING]

810
01:02:20,369 --> 01:02:21,971
Surprise, surprise, huh?

811
01:02:24,941 --> 01:02:25,942
Come here.

812
01:03:12,121 --> 01:03:14,090
[SHRIEKING]

813
01:03:14,123 --> 01:03:17,593
JOE: Hey, what-- what are you
doing?

814
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:18,594
[GRUNTING]

815
01:03:18,628 --> 01:03:20,196
[SHRIEKING]

816
01:03:25,101 --> 01:03:28,070
[THUMPING]

817
01:03:35,344 --> 01:03:38,614
Who is your boss?

818
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:40,917
What are you talking about,
boss?

819
01:03:40,950 --> 01:03:43,519
Head of your organization.

820
01:03:43,553 --> 01:03:45,054
JOE: I--

821
01:03:45,087 --> 01:03:46,055
Answer me.

822
01:03:46,088 --> 01:03:47,023
